WEBVTT

00:00:01.120 --> 00:00:12.640
<v Speaker 1>We also said that when we use ser or estar with an adjective plus que, so for example, es relevante que it's relevant that.

00:00:12.599 --> 00:00:15.960
<v Speaker 1>Esta bien que it's okay that.

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:20.279
<v Speaker 1>We will follow this up with the mood tense.

00:00:20.279 --> 00:00:27.160
<v Speaker 1>So how would you say for example, it's not very relevant.

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:29.220
<v Speaker 1>that they found it.

00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:33.460
<v Speaker 1>It's not very relevant that they found it, for example.

00:00:33.460 --> 00:00:37.140
<v Speaker 1>So how is it's not very relevant?

00:00:37.719 --> 00:00:39.879
<v Speaker 2>No es muy relevante.

00:00:39.879 --> 00:00:43.399
<v Speaker 1>Good that they found it.

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:50.480
<v Speaker 2>Lo encontraran.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:51.200
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:00:51.200 --> 00:00:55.120
<v Speaker 1>Noes muy relevante que lo encontraran.

00:00:55.120 --> 00:00:57.520
<v Speaker 1>So here we're not starting with the past, are we?

00:00:57.520 --> 00:00:59.760
<v Speaker 1>Noes muy relevante.

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:00.820
<v Speaker 1>That's the present.

00:01:00.820 --> 00:01:06.340
<v Speaker 1>But after care we refer back to the past, so we can use the past mood tense.

00:01:06.340 --> 00:01:09.060
<v Speaker 1>In the same way, we could use the present mood tense.

00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:14.660
<v Speaker 1>We could say it's not very relevant that they find it, that they might find it.

00:01:14.460 --> 00:01:28.220
<v Speaker 1>using the present mood tense so how would that sound no es muy relevante que lo encuentren que lo encuentren good

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:32.360
<v Speaker 1>How would you say it wasn't very relevant?

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:39.400
<v Speaker 1>Now the line, we can use the line in the past here, from ser is irregular.

00:01:39.400 --> 00:01:43.400
<v Speaker 1>But we can remember the word era in English.

00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:51.000
<v Speaker 1>To remember this line in the past from Sir, because a line in the past is an era, and if we pronounce era as if

00:01:50.900 --> 00:01:52.980
<v Speaker 1>If it was Spanish, we get era.

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:53.460
<v Speaker 1>Era.

00:01:53.460 --> 00:01:55.700
<v Speaker 1>And that's the line in the past from ser.

00:01:55.700 --> 00:01:59.540
<v Speaker 1>So how would you say it was very relevant?

00:02:02.280 --> 00:02:02.600
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:04.840
<v Speaker 1>It was very relevant that they found it.

00:02:04.840 --> 00:02:07.800
<v Speaker 1>It was very relevant that they found it.

00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:13.660
<v Speaker 2>Era muy relevante que lo encontraron.

00:02:13.660 --> 00:02:15.260
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:18.540
<v Speaker 1>So we want to identify the structures.

00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:26.840
<v Speaker 1>that allow us to use the mood tense other than to use the mood tense correctly to also avoid it sometimes

00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:27.320
<v Speaker 1>No?

00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:38.360
<v Speaker 1>So imagine you're having a conversation and you just want to get the meaning across and the point across and maybe you don't want to worry in that moment about finding the mood tense.

00:02:38.120 --> 00:02:44.920
<v Speaker 1>You just have something you need to say and you will worry about it later how how it would be with the moot tense.

00:02:44.920 --> 00:02:48.520
<v Speaker 1>So we can play around with the structure as we did

00:02:48.560 --> 00:03:02.799
<v Speaker 1>For example, with Volvia Llamarte para organizar, I called you again to organize, instead of Volvia Llamarte para que organizáramos, I called you again so that we organized.

00:03:02.799 --> 00:03:09.760
<v Speaker 1>Like we did there, we can play around a little bit with the structure to avoid using the mood tense.

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:17.360
<v Speaker 1>So for example, instead of saying es importante que, we could also say the important thing is that.

00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:22.280
<v Speaker 1>And when we say the important thing is that, what we end up with is Ske.

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:29.240
<v Speaker 1>So we said that we have a useful structure that we can use to give this the important thing.

00:03:28.980 --> 00:03:38.980
<v Speaker 1>So instead of saying la cosa importante, which would be a literal translation of the important thing, how can we make that structure using law?

00:03:39.880 --> 00:03:41.720
<v Speaker 2>To say lo importante?

00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:42.280
<v Speaker 1>Yes.

00:03:42.280 --> 00:03:43.640
<v Speaker 1>Lo importante.

00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:44.040
<v Speaker 1>Good.

